article_title: Investors Debate the End of the Health-Care Stock Surge
article_text:
The thriving health-care sector is starting to look too rich for some investors’ taste.

Health-care companies in the S&P 500, ranging from health insurers to medical-device makers to biotechnology firms, have risen 26% in the past year. That is the largest increase among S&P 500 sectors and more than three times the 7.7% gain in the S&P 500 in the same period.

Strong earnings and revenue have fueled the gains,...
